0the%20Bronx%2C%20it%20will%20serve%20as%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20former%20president%20to%20further%20pursue%20his%20national%20strategy%20to%20win%20over%20minority%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2246973039-d619-4998-8e4e-2486191caa94%5C%22%3ETrump%20makes%20inroads%20with%20Black%20and%20Latino%20voters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20virtually%20no%20chance%20that%20Trump%20will%20actually%20win%20the%20Bronx%20in%20November.%20The%20borough%20has%20backed%20every%20Democratic%20presidential%20nominee%20since%201928.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Trump%20managed%20to%20improve%20his%20standing%20with%20Bronx%20voters%2C%20if%20only%20slightly%2C%20winning%20nearly%2030%2C000%20more%20votes%20in%20the%20Bronx%20than%20he%20did%20in%202016.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20Democratic%20presidential%20vote%20share%20went%20up%20by%20only%202%2C000%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Biden%20ultimately%20clobbered%20Trump%20in%20the%20Bronx%20(355%2C374%20votes%20to%2067%2C740%20votes)%20in%202020%2C%20the%20boost%20for%20the%20ex-president%20was%20similar%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-florida-support-polling-latino-black-voters-evangelicals-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egains%20he%20made%20with%20working-class%20minority%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20Latino%20voters%20%E2%80%94%20across%20the%20country%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20political%20shift%20that%20in%202020%20allowed%20Trump%20to%20easily%20win%20Florida%2C%20including%20the%20pivotal%20Miami-Dade%20County%2C%20a%20Latino-heavy%20jurisdiction%20that%20Democrats%20have%20to%20carry%20by%20a%20substantial%20margin%20in%20order%20to%20win%20statewide%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20New%20York%20City%20isn't%20Florida%2C%20Trump's%20campaign%20event%20in%20the%20Bronx%20is%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20strategy%20to%20win%20over%20minority%20voters%20who%20have%20drifted%20away%20from%20the%20Democrats%20in%20