gular%20sauna%20sessions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20benefit%20individuals%20with%20depression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMason%20and%20her%20team%20conducted%20a%20clinical%20trial%20on%2012%20adults%20with%20major%20depressive%20disorder%20over%20eight%20weeks.%20They%20treated%20them%20with%20a%20combination%20of%20cognitive%20behavioral%20therapy%20and%20sessions%20in%20a%20sauna%20heated%20to%20about%20101.3%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20for%20up%20to%20140%20minutes.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20trial%2C%2011%20out%20of%20the%2012%20participants%20no%20longer%20met%20the%20criteria%20for%20major%20depressive%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20study's%20key%20ideas%20concerns%20body%20temperature.%20Research%20shows%20that%20individuals%20with%20depression%20often%20have%20a%20higher-than-average%20body%20temperature.%20When%20someone's%20symptoms%20improve%2C%20their%20body%20temperature%20normalizes%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20raises%20the%20hypothesis%3A%20If%20you%20drive%20up%20body%20temperatures%2C%20can%20you%20get%20the%20body's%20cooling%20systems%20to%20work%20faster%20and%20mitigate%20the%20symptoms%20of%20depression%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20idea%20has%20long%20been%20circulating%20among%20researchers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamapsychiatry%2Ffullarticle%2F2521478%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%202016%20found%20that%20people%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fwhat-is-depression%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emajor%20depressive%20disorder%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20went%20through%20%26quot%3Binfrared%20hyperthermia%26quot%3B%E2%80%94%20increasing%20their%20body%20temperatures%20in%20an%20infrared%20chamber%E2%80%94%20saw%20an%20improvement%20in%20depression%20symptoms.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMason%20told%20Wired%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bbewitched%26quot%3B%20by%20those%20findings%2C%20so%20as%20part%20of%20her%20work%2C%20she%20and%20her%20team%20analyzed%20daily%20temperature%20readings%20and%20depression%20symptoms%20from%20over%2020%2C000%20people%20to%20confirm%20the%20link%20between%20the%20two.%20All%20participants%20in%20Mason's%20study%20also%20saw%20their%20body%20temperature%20increase%20by%201.5%20degrees%20above%20the%20average%20human%20temperature%20during%20their%20sauna%20sessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMason%20said%20there's%20still%20more%20research%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20before%20she%20can%20confirm%20that%20sauna%20therapy%20can%20combat%20depression.%20But%20%26quot%3Ba%20mind%20and%20body%20treatment%20with%20that%20kind%20of%20outcome%20is%20surely%20worthy%20of%20further%20study%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fsauna-heat-therapy-depression-cbt-mental-health-trial%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eshe%20told%20Wired%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20eventually%20wants%20to%20gather%20enough%20clinical%20evidence%20for%20insurance%20companies%20to%20cover%20saunas%20%26quot%3Bso%20that%20when%20a%20person%20with%20depression%20is%20considering%20a%20menu%20of%20treatment%20options%2C%20this%20is%20on%20the%20menu.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20therapists%20are%20already%20recommending%20sauna%20therapy%20to%20their%20clients.%20%26quot%3BMy%20clients%20have%20reported%20positive%20mood-enhancing%20benefits%2C%20including%20some%20alleviation%20of%20their%20depression%20symptoms%20during%20and%20in%20the%20time%20after%20using%20saunas%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-therapist-seeing-panic-anxiety-amid-tech-layoffs-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAnnie%20Wright%2C%20a%20licensed%20psychotherapist%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20who's%20been%20practicing%20for%20over%2014%20years%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C