C%22engagement%22%3A681%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Flive%2Fworld-middle-east-69035051%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Delhi%20Records%20Hottest%20Day%20Of%20Season%20At%2044.4%20Degress%2C%20Harsher%20Days%20Ahead%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDelhi%2C%20which%20has%20been%20reeling%20under%20unbearable%20heat%2C%20experienced%20the%20season's%20hottest%20day%20so%20far%20with%20a%20scalding%20temperature%20of%2044.4%20degrees%20Celsius.%20This%20comes%20amid%20'red%20alert'%20warning%20by%20the%20weather%20department%20that%20predicted%20heat%20wave%20conditions%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20city%20over%20the%20next%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20capital's%20base%20weather%20station%20at%20Safdarjung%20recorded%20a%20high%20of%2044.4%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20which%20was%20more%20than%20three%20notches%20above%20the%20season's%20normal%20and%20the%20highest%20maximum%20temperature%20this%20season%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENajafgarh%20station%20in%20West%20Delhi%20recorded%20the%20highest%20of%20all%20stations%20in%20Delhi%20today%20i.e%2047.8%20degrees%20followed%20by%20Mungeshpur%20station%20that%20recorded%2047.7%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20(IMD)%20mentioned%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20heat%20wave%20in%20its%20seven-day%20forecast%20and%20urged%20extreme%20care%20for%20vulnerable%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20very%20high%20likelihood%20of%20developing%20heat%20illness%20and%20heat%20stroke%20in%20people%20of%20all%20ages%2C%20and%20a%20health%20concern%20for%20vulnerable%20individuals%20such%20as%20infants%2C%20the%20elderly%2C%20and%20those%20with%20chronic%20diseases%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAvoid%20heat%20exposure%20and%20keep%20cool.%20Avoid%20dehydration%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20spells%20of%20ex